Arsène Wenger happy to see Arsenal win ugly after win over Southampton takes Gunners four points clear
Arsenal manager claims victory proves that his team have developed another asset in pursuit of the Premier League title.
Pyhtonesque: Southampton goalkeeper Artur Boruc (right) dithers to allow Olivier Giroud to put Arsenal ahead Photo: GETTY IMAGES	By Jim White
11:00PM GMT 24 Nov 2013
Follow Comments
Arsène Wenger had little doubt what victory against a resolute, determined Southampton side meant. “This win shows we are ready for a fight when it doesn’t go as fluently as we wanted,” the Arsenal manager said. “On that front I’m very happy today.” After the defeat against Manchester United this 2-0 victory at the Emirates Stadium was just what Wenger needed to demonstrate his side’s title credentials. It was, in short, the very definition of the old saw about champions triumphing in scrappy victory. Never mind the quality, feel the win.
